    "attributes": {
        "action": "Establish new Hallowe\u2019en public holiday in England and Wales",
        "additional_details": "Hallowe\u2019en is a popular celebration for many, and it is placed mid-way between the August bank holiday and Christmas.\r\n\r\nIn England and Wales, there is a huge, 4-month gap between the August bank holiday and Christmas.\r\n\r\nA Halloween public holiday would dovetail nicely with half-term school holidays in many parts of the country.\r\n\r\nOne-offs like the 2022 Platinum Jubilee or a potential major sports win like UEFA\u2019s Euro 2024 are far from enough for the British public who have experienced major stress and exhaustion during the not yet finished pandemic years.",
        "background": "With only 8 public holidays a year, England & Wales rank as the worst in Europe, as countries on the continent have an average of around 12 public holidays a year.",
